SIMPLE: strangulation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strangulation
<hw>Stran"gu*la`tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>strangulatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>strangulation</ets>. See
<er>Strangle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of strangling, or the
state of being strangled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Inordinate compression or
constriction of a tube or part, as of the throat; especially, such as
causes a suspension of breathing, of the passage of contents, or of the
circulation, as in cases of hernia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strangurious</ent>⟦br⟧
